    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Neuroligins Interact with Gephyrin\"\nFig.2: \"The Interaction of NL2 with Gephyrin Promotes Coclustering in Neurons\"\nFig.4: \"NL2 Is Required for Proper GABAergic and Glycinergic but Not Glutamatergic Transmission in the Brainstem\"\nFig.5: \"NL2-/- Neurons in Culture Display Deficits in Postsynaptic Targeting of Gephyrin at Perisomatic Synapses\"\nFig.6: \"GABAergic Transmission and Postsynaptic Differentiation Are Perturbed at Perisomatic Synapses in the Hippocampus of NL2-/- Mice\". Experimental description: - Overexpressed NLGN2; neuroligin 2 is of rat species; \"The GST-NL2CD construct was created by subcloning the rat NL2 cytoplasmic domain sequence into vector pGEX-4T1\"\n- \"Hippocampal neurons were prepared from P0 NL2-/- mice....\"\n- \"Immunolabeling of Brain Sections: Eight-week-old male NL2-/- and NL2+/+ ...\"\n- \"Electrophysiological Recordings: All electrophysiological analyses were performed on brainstem neurons or CA1 pyramidal neurons of mice \"",
